10/04/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The government has passed a draft law, envisioning up to 20 years imprisonment for tax evasion, Prime Minister Calin Popescu Tariceanu announced on Friday (8 April). 
The bill is expected to strengthen the fight against financial crime and corruption, he said, adding that the draft is aimed at harmonising Romanian legislation with European standards. 
It also fulfils commitments made in the Anticorruption Strategy Action Plan, sent to Brussels recently. 
(Nine o'clock - 08/04/05)
